The paper discusses a remote code injection attack on a wireless sensor network device with limited memory and a Harvard architecture CPU. This makes it likely to fall under the categories of computer security (cs.CR), embedded systems (cs.EM), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), and software engineering (cs.SE).
